                   "message":  "MENUARC-DOC-RECONCILE-A4: reconcile A4 docs after the View menu landed (#299)\n\nForward-only planning-substrate hygiene after #299 (be4896a,\nVIEWMENU-RESETCAMERA-A4) added the View menu (Reset Camera), closing the\nmenu-breadth arc (File/Edit/Play/View). Prepends a new 2026-06-03 A4 snapshot to\nStatus.md + HANDOFF.md, inserts a new \"2026-06-03 - View menu now\nregistry-produced; menu-breadth arc complete (#299 A4)\" subsection into\nplans/BASELINE.md above the A3 subsection, and appends a matching change.md\nentry. All A3/A2/A1 snapshots, subsections, and entries are byte-identical (pure\nprepend/insert/append, +22/-0).\n\nRecords that View is no longer the lone remaining standard menu: unlike A1-A3\n(pure wiring), View needed a new runtime action (EditorShell::reset_camera +\ncurrent_scene_bounds, frame-the-scene), wired via Command::ResetCamera. Notes the\n// SPLIT-EXEMPTION: annotation on editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs and the flagged\nEGUIHOST-TEST-EXTRACTION follow-up. No standard menus remain deferred; the\npost-breadth frontier is registry/accelerator execution + plugins + predicates +\nper-frame re-resolve.\n\nDocs-only: no Rust source / test / Cargo / rustdoc / lint-doc change (the menu\nrustdoc was widened to File + Edit + Play + View inside #299 itself).\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only; no Rust touched).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
